===Verb===
'''zullen''' (irregular verb)

# {{context|lang=nl|modal auxiliary}} Used to indicate [[intent]] or [[disposition]] to perform an action in the [[future]]: [[will]], [[shall]], be [[going to]].
#: ''Dat zou ik niet doen.'' &mdash; I would not do that.
#: ''Het zou gaan regenen.'' &mdash; It was going to rain.
#: ''Zal ik eerst gaan?'' &mdash; Shall I go first?
# {{context|lang=nl|auxiliary}} Used to form the [[future tense]] of a verb, together with an [[infinitive]].
#: ''Het zal toch niet werken.'' &mdash; It will not work anyway.
#: ''Dat zal niet gebeuren.'' &mdash; That will not happen.
#: '''Note:''' [[gaan]] is also used for the future tense, instead of zullen.

